title: Driver's Education Supplemental Parent Class draws in close to 40
text: Driver's Education Supplemental Parent Class draws in close to 40 Presentations by Minnesota State Patrol officer Brad Norland, Crookston Police Chief Paul Biermaier, Drivers Ed instructor Chris Trostad and Behind the Wheel instructor Rodd Olson on safe driving, statistics and upcoming new laws got parents thinking about their soon-to-be drivers. Comment By Times Report Posted Jul. 29, 2015 at 10:51 AM Crookston Police Chief Paul Biermaier talks about the new texting while driving law that goes into effect August 1st. By Times Report Posted Jul. 29, 2015 at 10:51 AM Crookston, Minn. Presentations by Minnesota State Patrol officer Brad Norland, Crookston Police Chief Paul Biermaier, Drivers Ed instructor Chris Trostad and Behind the Wheel instructor Rodd Olson on safe driving, statistics and upcoming new laws got parents thinking about their soon-to-be drivers. By Times Report
